License: MIT
Description: OffDocumentation - Download Docs from ReadTheDocs

        ==============================================

        

        |License| |Development Status|

        

        OffDocumentation is a python 2/3 module/utility to download Documenation

        hosted on ReadTheDocs in HTML, PDF and EPUB Formats

        

        It can be used from the terminal or by using the API.

        

        Installation

        ------------

        

        Installing is simple, just enter this command:

        

        ::

        

            pip install OffDocumentation

        

        You need to have pip installed to run this command

        

        Usage

        -----

        

        Just run the following command:

        

        ::

        

            offdocumentation [-f format] [-d directory] url/package name

        

        For example,

        

        ::

        

            offdocumentation -f HTML flask

        

        or

        

        ::

        

            offdocumentation -f epub http://scrapy.readthedocs.org/en/latest/

        

        API Usage

        ---------

        

        You can use the module from python also. Example code:

        

        .. code:: python

        

            from offdocumentation import offdocumentation

            DocDwn=offdocumentation('flask','pdf')

            DocDwn.download()

        

        Dependencies

        ------------

        

        1. requests

        2. BeautifulSoup4

        3. wget (the python module)

        
    

